          Full job description

          • Job ID:

            J50241

          • Job Title:

            Sr. Power BI Developer and Analyst

          • Location:

            Minneapolis,, MN

          • Duration:

            14 Months + Extension

          • Hourly Rate:

            Depending on Experience (DOE)

          • Work Authorization:

            US Citizen, Green Card, OPT-EAD, CPT, H-1B,
            H4-EAD, L2-EAD, GC-EAD

          • Client:

            To Be Discussed Later

          • Employment Type:

            W-2, 1099, C2C


          Job Details

          Short list of skills required:


          PowerBI Report Development, including modeling, performance optimization techniques, visualization design, Power Query and DAX.
          Experience with Azure SQL Database
          SQL skills with expertise in windowed functions and performance tuning.
          Analytics skills - working with stakeholders gathering requirements

          Full list of must have skills:


          Exceptional Azure SQL skills
          Expertise in Windowed functions
          Performance tuning.
          Has direct experience building and troubleshooting complex views and stored procedures.
          Understands the difference between CTEs, temp tables, variable tables and the appropriate time to use them.
          Has created SQL tables and know the nuances of indexing practices.
          Has worked in a Datawarehouse environment before leveraging type 2 SLD.
          Advanced knowledge of Power BI
          Data modeling techniques
          Report performance optimization best practices
          Visualization design
          Power Query
          DAX
          Has extensive experience working in the Power BI service
          Has administered power BI workspaces, pushing from dev->test->prod and updating associated apps.
          Understands Power BI Deployment pipelines
          Experience with Power BI GIT workspace integration
          Communication Skills - Will need to work directly with the business and IT Leadership.
          Will be managing relationships with stakeholders in the business.
          Will need to be prompt following up with support incidents.
          Nice to have:


          Python
          Microsoft Fabric
          Azure Data Factory
          Power Automate
          Azure Functions
          Azure storage accounts
